Elements of annotate()

https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/index.html https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/annotate.html

storms %>% 
  filter(Year >= 1950) %>% 
ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = Hurricanes)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  annotate(
    "rect", 
    xmin = c(2002.5, 2017.5),
    xmax = c(2007.5, 2022.5),
    ymin = c(14, 13), 
    ymax = c(16, 15),
    color = "black",
    fill = "lightblue",
    alpha = 0.25) +
  annotate(
    "label",
    x = c(2005, 2020),
    y = c(17, 16),
    label = c("2005", "2020"),
    fill = "lightblue"
  ) +
  annotate(
    "curve",
    x = 1980,
    y = 14,
    xend = 1970,
    yend = 12.25,
    arrow = arrow(length = unit(0.3, 'cm'))
  ) +
  annotate(
    "label",
    x = 1980,
    y = 13,
    label = "1969"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1950, 2023, 10)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 18, 2), limits = c(0, 18)) +
  labs(
    title = "Atlantic Ocean Hurricanes Per Year 1950 to 2023",
    subtitle = "Hurricane season is approximately June through November",
    x = "year",
    y = "number of hurricanes"
  ) +
  theme_linedraw()

Elements of theme()

https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/index.html https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/theme.html https://www.statology.org/rotate-axis-labels-ggplot2/

storms %>% 
  filter(Year >= 2000) %>% 
ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = Hurricanes)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.5, color = "blue", fill = "lightblue") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2000, 2023, 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 15, 1)) +
  labs(
    title = "Atlantic Ocean Hurricanes Per Year 2000 to 2023",
    subtitle = "Hurricane season is approximately June through November",
    x = "year",
    y = "number of hurricanes"
  ) +
  theme(
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA, color = "black"),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.major.y = element_line(color = "lightgray"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, color = "red"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, color = "blue")
  )

mycooltheme <- theme(
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA, color = "black"),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
